  "response": "The \"Russian Sleep Experiment\" is a well-known urban legend and creepypasta that circulated on the internet. It tells a fictional story about a supposed Soviet-era experiment during which scientists used a gas to keep five people awake for 15 days. The narrative describes horrific psychological and physical effects on the subjects as they descend into madness, leading to self-mutilation and violent behavior.\n\nDespite its popularity in horror and speculative fiction, there is no evidence to suggest that such an experiment ever took place. It is entirely a work of fiction designed to evoke fear and explore themes related to sleep deprivation and the human psyche. The story has been rehashed in various forms, including short films and other creative works, but it should be regarded as a fictional tale rather than a factual account.",
